    "created_at": "2015-07-30T01:46:38Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-30T01:46:38Z",
    "body": "Whether to show shadow for a frameless window completely depends on the window manager, on OS X the real frameless window doesn't have shadow too and it is fixed by using a window with frame while resizing the content area to covert the frame. However I don't think there is a way to fix this on Linux, because the frame and shadow are drawn by the window manager.\n"
